top source get_distdopp_bytime

result = get_distdopp_bytime(time, time_in_s=time_in_s, verbose=verbose, use_interpol=use_interpol, debug=debug)

NAME: get_distdopp_bytime PURPOSE: Return Distance and Doppler factors from provided resource USAGE: dd=get_distdopp_bytime(time ,[USE_interpol=use_interpol][,TIME_IN_S=time_in_s][VERBOSE=VERBOSE]) OPTIONAL INPUT PARAMETERS: TIME_IN_S : Set if input is in seconds, output time will also be in seconds. Default = 0, Indicating that input and output time are in milli-seconds. USE_INTERPOL : Set to use the IDL Interpol function instead of linterp (default=TRUE) VERBOSE : Set if reporting of details is desired (default=0)

Parameters

time
